## The Verdict

A **1 carat round diamond** at the quality level most buyers need — GIA Excellent, G color, VS1 clarity — costs **$3,200 to $3,840** at Blue Nile in {{year}}. The three buying rules that prevent overpayment:

1. **Never sacrifice cut for any other variable.** GIA Excellent is mandatory.
2. **Use the Magic Carat Trap.** 0.90ct at identical quality is $640–$960 less for zero visible size difference.
3. **Buy G or H color.** D–F color is invisible in wear and costs $800–$1,200 more.

If natural origin does not matter: the lab-grown [D-IF Ideal at $1,560](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28023534?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the best 1ct round diamond value in the market.

